pddl_domain_generation.prompt:
Here is the natural language description of the domain:
{environment->inputs->domain_nl}

Here is the PDDL domain template:
{environment->inputs->domain_template}

Fill in the predicates and complete the precondition and effect clauses for all actions in the domain template. Output only the complete and valid PDDL domain file, enclosed in <domain></domain> tags.

pddl_problem_generation.prompt:
Here is the PDDL domain that defines the predicates and actions:
{pddl_draft_domain}

Here is the natural language description of the problem:
{environment->inputs->problem_nl}

Here is the PDDL problem template which already includes objects and the goal state, but needs accurate initialization predicates based on the NL problem description:
{environment->inputs->problem_template}

Review the initial state in the problem template against the NL description, and ensure all facts are correctly included and consistent with the domain's predicates. Output only the complete and valid PDDL problem file, enclosed in <problem></problem> tags.

final_pddl_assembly.prompt:
The generated PDDL Domain is:
{pddl_draft_domain}

The generated PDDL Problem is:
{pddl_draft_problem}

Review both files for consistency. Output the finalized PDDL Domain file enclosed in <domain></domain> tags, and the finalized PDDL Problem file enclosed in <problem></problem> tags.
